The paper deals with a geometric set cover problem involving unit disks, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the problem is NP-hard and admits a polynomial-time approximation scheme (PTAS), indicating that it may also belong to the approximation algorithms (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the minimum weight dominating set problem and the connected dominating set problem in unit disk graphs, which suggests that it may belong to the graph theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimization and algorithm design, which suggests that it may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
